      "message": "Tiling is a concept that we use for decomposition of the layer\u0027s entire contents at a picture screenspace resolution so that we could do multithreaded rasterization. For example, a 512x512 layer might have a tiling into 4 256x256 tiles for a 1:1 ratio of screenspace pixels to content pixels.\nThe metrics record how much GPU memory we allocate for a composited scrollable area, or how many tiles the scroller occupies. When there is no picture layer in the active tree we don\u0027t need to record anything as there is nothing to record.",
